The office shall immediately be deemed vacant.

1124
01:33:22,284 --> 01:33:37,663
For ward eligibility, we do have a school committee candidate shall be at the time of election to be a Medford voter and shall have resided in the ward they wish to represent for one year prior to submitting nomination papers for the office of school committee.

1125
01:33:38,003 --> 01:33:40,726
And again, it doesn't have to be that date.

1126
01:33:41,555 --> 01:33:51,025
But trying to make a distinction is if someone wants to represent a certain ward, shouldn't they have lived in that ward for some period of time?

1127
01:33:51,205 --> 01:33:52,526
Now, there was a debate about that.

1128
01:33:53,067 --> 01:33:58,272
And we may ultimately come back to that to be in line with the city council people.

1129
01:33:58,312 --> 01:34:00,274
But that's how we've written it at this time.

1130
01:34:02,416 --> 01:34:04,178
Do we have questions or should I just keep on moving?

1131
01:34:06,628 --> 01:34:07,389
Is that a hand?

1132
01:34:07,949 --> 01:34:15,655
Maybe it's a question, but the saying Medford voter versus Medford resident is that is it required that your voter to run for resident is fine.

