1140
01:34:32,708 --> 01:34:33,009
Go ahead.

1141
01:34:35,029 --> 01:34:39,038
Can you say more about your decision to leave the mayor as chair?

1142
01:34:41,365 --> 01:34:43,226
So that was a very complex discussion.

1143
01:34:43,866 --> 01:34:47,889
Ultimately, we had talked to all three mayors.

1144
01:34:48,589 --> 01:35:05,280
All three mayors thought it was a very key part of their job as the mayor, that the largest proportion of the budget is the school committee, and that it gave them a real understanding of all the school committee issues.

1145
01:35:05,800 --> 01:35:07,461
It also was, as we talked about it,

1146
01:35:09,362 --> 01:35:16,724
if you're going for the voting by ward, you've got, it's the mayor who's voted by all of the population.

1147
01:35:18,325 --> 01:35:28,428
And, you know, again, I felt strongly as someone who had been on the school committee that it was very, very valuable to have the mayor.

1148
01:35:29,188 --> 01:35:35,510
So with other people, ultimately, you know, this went back and forth and back and forth.

1149
01:35:37,602 --> 01:35:44,345
you know, with some people disagreeing and, um, you know, this is where we landed.

1150
01:35:45,346 --> 01:35:45,546
Okay.

1151
01:35:45,606 --> 01:35:51,728
And I add something that I learned during the process was that the mayor's vote counts the same as everybody else's vote.

1152
01:35:52,189 --> 01:36:04,374
And also as chair, their job is to, um, put together the agenda and maybe be less involved in some of the conversations that have that happened during the meeting.

1153
01:36:05,875 --> 01:36:06,115
Okay.

1154
01:36:08,227 --> 01:36:14,091
And what did this, because you interviewed the school committee members, what did they, did they weigh in on that?

1155
01:36:14,392 --> 01:36:15,572
Oh, it was very split.

1156
01:36:16,293 --> 01:36:22,578
There were some committee members who really didn't want the mayor as chair, and there were some who really did want the mayor's chair.

1157
01:36:22,618 --> 01:36:23,338
It's very split.

1158
01:36:23,658 --> 01:36:29,703
And with all of this, I mean, that's one of the things that I found is whoever you talk to, it was the next opinion.

1159
01:36:29,723 --> 01:36:31,544
And if there was,

1160
01:36:33,085 --> 01:36:37,208
if there was more of uniformity of our agreement, but there wasn't.

1161
01:36:38,869 --> 01:36:40,209
And we're doing the best we can.

1162
01:36:40,470 --> 01:36:53,798
And in the, you know, it's very interesting to get the mayor's feedback and where they had come from and sort of saying is that they were the ones who were elected by everybody.

1163
01:36:53,838 --> 01:36:57,500
And we are going to award, you know, representation.

1164
01:37:00,203 --> 01:37:29,438
So I don't know if any of the members of the committee want to speak to it, but I think what swayed me, I was in the, I don't think the mayor should be chair camp, but I think after hearing from, you know, through Paulette, hearing from Mayor McGlynn, Mayor Burke, and Mayor Longo Kern,

1165
01:37:30,164 --> 01:37:48,515
as to the value that all three of them put on their role, where they said that they were in front of the community, required to be in front of the community every other Monday, that was sacred to them.

1166
01:37:49,876 --> 01:37:58,421
And that, as she said, the school committee is the largest portion of the budget and that,

1167
01:37:59,580 --> 01:38:00,002
The mayor.

1168
01:38:01,203 --> 01:38:02,924
doesn't speak as much.

1169
01:38:03,224 --> 01:38:10,567
And if he or she does speak, they always speak last after they've heard from all of their colleagues.

1170
01:38:11,188 --> 01:38:16,590
So they have a good sense of the issues and concerns and so forth.

1171
01:38:16,650 --> 01:38:30,757
So that's what swayed me, the value that the three mayors that we've had, you know, in throughout most of my life, the value that they put on it that put me in the, you know, it's a good idea camp.

1172
01:38:31,525 --> 01:38:38,090
And what was so interesting about that was, however different they were, there was a consensus.

1173
01:38:39,071 --> 01:38:40,792
And we weren't talking at the same time.

1174
01:38:40,812 --> 01:38:43,694
I was talking to them individually.

1175
01:38:44,735 --> 01:38:48,818
So that, I think, was one of the reasons.

1176
01:38:50,762 --> 01:38:54,283
You know, a lot of people had talked about about power.

1177
01:38:54,303 --> 01:38:55,643
We're giving them too much power.

1178
01:38:55,683 --> 01:39:07,267
And then sort of saying is, boy, you want that mayor to know your school issues and understand your school issues and what it means to those kids, to each and every one.

1179
01:39:07,367 --> 01:39:10,067
And there is no better way than being present at the meetings.

1180
01:39:11,928 --> 01:39:14,729
So anyway, that's that's where we we landed.

1181
01:39:18,350 --> 01:39:23,613
And I should say throughout this, the one thing about our subcommittee is there was a lot of movement.

1182
01:39:24,273 --> 01:39:33,319
And sometimes I feel, just my little editorial, you know, there's not a lot now of coming together.

1183
01:39:33,379 --> 01:39:38,402
And in this subcommittee, we really worked to try and figure those things out.

1184
01:39:40,383 --> 01:39:41,343
Ron and then Danielle?

1185
01:39:47,107 --> 01:39:47,287
Ron?

1186
01:39:48,137 --> 01:39:49,679
Ron, you're muted.

1187
01:39:51,562 --> 01:39:52,484
My 1st comment is to.

1188
01:39:52,524 --> 01:39:58,192
No, but do you think we should be going through this section by section gaining agreement and then.

1189
01:39:58,693 --> 01:40:02,319
Make it easier to do the whole document, or do you want to just fly through it?

1190
01:40:02,835 --> 01:40:04,556
That's a good question.

1191
01:40:05,397 --> 01:40:09,340
I thought you guys would give a presentation and then people would sort of study it.

1192
01:40:09,520 --> 01:40:12,443
And then at the next meeting, we would vote on things.

1193
01:40:12,823 --> 01:40:13,423
Yeah, that's fine.

1194
01:40:13,443 --> 01:40:14,304
I just didn't know.

1195
01:40:14,764 --> 01:40:16,526
I don't want to just go back and forth.

1196
01:40:16,626 --> 01:40:17,407
And that's fine.

1197
01:40:17,567 --> 01:40:17,887
I get it.

1198
01:40:19,724 --> 01:40:21,085
Yeah.

1199
01:40:21,565 --> 01:40:22,686
Is that what you thought, Paula?

1200
01:40:23,066 --> 01:40:23,286
Yes.

1201
01:40:23,366 --> 01:40:26,428
I thought that I was just sort of giving an overview of the most important parts.

1202
01:40:28,089 --> 01:40:29,910
That's fine.

1203
01:40:29,930 --> 01:40:30,411
That's fine.

1204
01:40:30,471 --> 01:40:30,551
Okay.

1205
01:40:30,571 --> 01:40:45,340
To the other question, I just want to say that, yes, Paula's right in terms of we came in with preconceived notions, of course, but the public participation was huge in a lot of this decision-making process.

1206
01:40:46,282 --> 01:40:48,864
The three interviews with the mayors was important.

1207
01:40:48,904 --> 01:40:53,227
We did interview the mayor of Malden, who did not think he had to be the chair of the committee.

1208
01:40:54,128 --> 01:41:00,193
And I deferred a lot, to be honest with you, to Paulette, who lived the life that we're trying to make easier.

1209
01:41:00,273 --> 01:41:05,257
So she was very strong in her opinion, and I support her 100%.

1210
01:41:05,297 --> 01:41:05,637
Danielle?

1211
01:41:05,657 --> 01:41:15,645
Yeah, I'm just going to ask on the question about the mayor being the chair, what our survey said of the

1212
01:41:16,398 --> 01:41:18,840
public, or like where that figured in?

1213
01:41:21,221 --> 01:41:27,446
I think that it was pretty mixed.

1214
01:41:27,566 --> 01:41:41,716
One of the difficulties that I have with that is that you ask people, like, I mean, I remember when we were at the wonderful Rights Pond event, and you were kind of asking people some of these questions, and they were thinking about these things off the top of their head.

1215
01:41:44,103 --> 01:41:55,649
While it was very useful to get as much feedback as possible, you know, there's, dare I say, many people who've never watched a school committee meeting.

1216
01:41:56,770 --> 01:41:58,751
So, you know, it's sort of like, ugh.

1217
01:42:01,523 --> 01:42:11,589
I don't know, I found it difficult to tell because obviously we wanted to take into account the public's opinions as much as possible.

1218
01:42:11,949 --> 01:42:16,471
And I think in terms of moving towards the wards, we did.

1219
01:42:18,753 --> 01:42:29,118
That was a big, I mean, because certainly for me, I had started out being completely at large and I certainly moved on that along the way.

1220
01:42:30,059 --> 01:42:30,379
Anthony?

1221
01:42:33,282 --> 01:42:37,203
I thank you all for the work you did on this committee.

1222
01:42:37,504 --> 01:42:41,325
I think you had a very challenging task.

1223
01:42:42,045 --> 01:42:44,345
I just want a couple of things.

1224
01:42:44,425 --> 01:42:53,568
As a parent who had children in Method Public Schools, I understand the importance of having a strong school committee.

1225
01:42:53,988 --> 01:43:00,550
And I think the presence of the mayor being on the school committee, for me, historically, when I

1226
01:43:01,572 --> 01:43:12,781
had some issues or challenging questions, I was on the phone with the mayor.

1227
01:43:13,722 --> 01:43:30,496
I feel that it's important for residents who have an issue with the schools to be able to reach their mayor and have their mayor intervene for them if something is

1228
01:43:31,750 --> 01:43:33,071
needs to be addressed.

1229
01:43:33,972 --> 01:43:56,631
And just one other thing about the mayor being on the school committee, given what we're facing with the opportunity of building a new high school for the future kids in Medford, the mayor's being part of the school committee and working together with the school committee is gonna be key to making that a reality.

1230
01:43:56,691 --> 01:43:58,273
And that's a task that

1231
01:43:58,833 --> 01:44:16,156
And I remember hearing somewhere that, you know, part of the reason that we got our elementary schools and were able to be so successful was that, you know, Mayor McGlynn was, you know, part of the school committee and really kind of was able to

1232
01:44:17,375 --> 01:44:20,897
put all the pieces together and get everybody on board.

1233
01:44:20,977 --> 01:44:35,446
And I think it's going to be important for the mayor to have that opportunity to kind of work with the school committee folks to have that vision become a reality because I think

1234
01:44:35,786 --> 01:44:38,148
you know, the kids need it, you know.

1235
01:44:38,408 --> 01:44:44,492
And it's not so much the politics of school committee, it's, you know, the results.

1236
01:44:44,992 --> 01:44:45,993
We need some results.

1237
01:44:46,133 --> 01:44:50,056
And I think it's important to hold the mayor accountable.

1238
01:44:50,316 --> 01:44:55,779
And that's a good way, like, to judge a mayor on, you know, should you vote to re-elect your mayors?

1239
01:44:55,879 --> 01:44:58,261
You know, how did they perform on the school committee?

1240
01:44:58,481 --> 01:45:00,182
You know, what did they do for the kids?

1241
01:45:00,823 --> 01:45:03,004
And I think...

1242
01:45:04,702 --> 01:45:05,923
Go ahead.

1243
01:45:05,943 --> 01:45:06,443
I'm sorry.

1244
01:45:06,483 --> 01:45:07,343
I ramble with them out.

1245
01:45:07,503 --> 01:45:08,564
No, no, I hear what you're saying.

1246
01:45:08,584 --> 01:45:14,906
I just want to be clear that at no time I don't think in this subcommittee do we think the mayor should not be on the school committee.

1247
01:45:14,926 --> 01:45:16,727
It was more about the chairperson.

1248
01:45:17,267 --> 01:45:20,468
It was more about, you know, that role.

1249
01:45:20,548 --> 01:45:31,933
But to answer Danielle's question, there were a lot of survey results that were against the mayor being the chairperson and a lot of interviews and feedback that we got

1250
01:45:33,233 --> 01:45:43,456
that were very, very powerful feedback that they thought that the job is better served by a different school committee.

1251
01:45:43,476 --> 01:45:48,378
So there were definitely, it wasn't like a landslide victory that we said the mayor should be chairman.

1252
01:45:48,418 --> 01:45:49,418
I just want to make that point.

1253
01:45:52,435 --> 01:45:57,899
OK, so I'm going to go on, I think, just so we can get through this because we're time is fleeting.

1254
01:45:59,280 --> 01:46:10,168
By the way, one question is we've traditionally in Medford always called the secretary secretary while clerk was shown in different documents.

1255
01:46:11,089 --> 01:46:18,194
And so the question ultimately was, do we go with what's traditional in Medford secretary or is there a preference for clerk?

1256
01:46:19,635 --> 01:46:22,137
I don't, you know,

1257
01:46:22,908 --> 01:46:23,268
I don't know.

1258
01:46:24,609 --> 01:46:35,037
Um, for the school committee organization, we had the mayor shall service chair of the school committee, and then the language about, you know, when they should take their positions.

1259
01:46:36,990 --> 01:46:45,360
And then the school committee members shall choose from amongst themselves a vice chair and a secretary who will each serve for one year.

1260
01:46:45,380 --> 01:46:54,751
The person, the position should rotate amongst members with no members serving more than one consecutive year in the role for which they have been selected for by their peers.

1261
01:46:55,832 --> 01:47:03,395
And that is something which I did speak to very specifically as from my time.

1262
01:47:03,495 --> 01:47:09,137
I think that the idea is not to then create a mini person in charge.

1263
01:47:09,197 --> 01:47:17,981
I think that you learn as you're a school committee member how to do that role, and it's important for it to rotate amongst members.

1264
01:47:18,801 --> 01:47:19,641
So we put that in.

1265
01:47:23,152 --> 01:47:24,812
The chair shall prepare the agenda.

1266
01:47:24,832 --> 01:47:28,733
There was a lot of concern that this gave the mayor too much work.

1267
01:47:28,773 --> 01:47:43,096
But but what and we we interviewed both Dr. The president, Superintendent Maurice Edouard Vincent and former Superintendent Roy Belson.

1268
01:47:43,696 --> 01:47:52,858
And, you know, the superintendent's office and the superintendent puts the agenda together and runs it by the mayor.

1269
01:47:54,099 --> 01:48:01,765
there is a process within the school committee, within their own rules, of making sure that they can put something on the agenda.

1270
01:48:03,146 --> 01:48:14,535
That the chair presides at all regular meetings, it regulates its proceedings, decides on all questions of order, and it doesn't say, by the way, that we run our

1271
01:48:16,076 --> 01:48:18,778
meetings by Robert's rules of order.

1272
01:48:18,818 --> 01:48:26,542
And I wondered for both the city council, whether at some point we ought to be making that clear, but that's how meetings are run.

1273
01:48:28,283 --> 01:48:34,005
The chair shall appoint all members of the school committee to the various subcommittees.

1274
01:48:34,746 --> 01:48:42,510
I did add the clause after seeking their individual input regarding interest in availability, because I always thought it was important that we got asked

1275
01:48:43,771 --> 01:48:49,235
The chair will have the same powers to vote upon measures coming before the school committee as any other member.

1276
01:48:50,296 --> 01:48:58,402
The vice chair presides in the absence of the chair, and the secretary both records the votes taken at a regular school committee meeting.

1277
01:48:58,782 --> 01:49:06,288
I should say there's also professional backup, but the secretary is the one who calls the rolls.

1278
01:49:07,389 --> 01:49:11,292
And in Medford, the secretary is responsible for overseeing and

1279
01:49:11,732 --> 01:49:13,574
approving the bills of the school department.

1280
01:49:15,717 --> 01:49:22,444
At some point, the school committee could form a subcommittee expressly for reviewing the bills.

1281
01:49:22,924 --> 01:49:24,606
That is not how we do it right now.

1282
01:49:26,408 --> 01:49:28,090
It has been discussed over time.

1283
01:49:28,551 --> 01:49:32,815
So at this right now, the secretary is the designated person.

1284
01:49:34,716 --> 01:49:38,058
And it's a very important role.

1285
01:49:39,278 --> 01:49:47,341
At school committee meetings, when the bills are presented, school committee members ask questions.

1286
01:49:47,921 --> 01:49:54,143
And very often when I was a secretary or someone else was the secretary, they would say, what about this expenditure?

1287
01:49:54,743 --> 01:49:56,844
And you would have actually seen the bill

1288
01:49:57,724 --> 01:50:02,207
And you would have, as the secretary, have a chance to ask questions about it.

1289
01:50:03,247 --> 01:50:11,552
By the way, the sign-off also is the finance person and the superintendent of schools also review the bills.

1290
01:50:12,492 --> 01:50:13,913
So that's how we do it now.

1291
01:50:15,234 --> 01:50:16,034
Limitations.

1292
01:50:17,795 --> 01:50:20,857
No member shall hold any other city office.

1293
01:50:21,077 --> 01:50:25,740
No former member of the school committee shall hold any compensated appointed city office.

1294
01:50:26,893 --> 01:50:30,135
until at least one year after the date of the member service on the school committee.

1295
01:50:30,175 --> 01:50:31,576
This is pretty standard language.

1296
01:50:32,697 --> 01:50:46,566
There was in the different ones, charters that we looked at this whole thing about, however, if someone has vacated a position in order to serve as a member of the school committee, they may return to the same office.

1297
01:50:48,087 --> 01:50:51,851
of city employment held at the time the position was vacated.

1298
01:50:52,412 --> 01:50:57,518
And Ron, you will remember we discussed this and I put in the clause, if it has remained vacant.

1299
01:50:59,162 --> 01:51:00,562
because we were worried about that.

1300
01:51:00,902 --> 01:51:02,103
That is not something we wrote.

1301
01:51:02,423 --> 01:51:05,523
We can go to the Collins and say, why is it in all these other charters?

1302
01:51:05,863 --> 01:51:08,284
But it was consistently in other charters.

1303
01:51:08,644 --> 01:51:13,225
And I don't know whether that's just because someone put it in and then someone else copied it and someone else copied it.

1304
01:51:13,325 --> 01:51:17,266
So, but that's how we wrote it here.

1305
01:51:18,866 --> 01:51:28,168
Compensation, we just said that, you know, I wanted to make sure we didn't work out terminology on this because it should be consistent with everyone else.

1306
01:51:29,371 --> 01:51:31,492
Section 4-5, powers and duties.

1307
01:51:32,252 --> 01:51:39,555
The first part of this was taken from the school committee powers and duties, which is outlined on their website.

1308
01:51:40,256 --> 01:51:45,518
This is standard put together by the Massachusetts Association of School Committees.

1309
01:51:46,318 --> 01:51:49,439
The Collins Center did say it was more detailed than other charters.

1310
01:51:50,580 --> 01:51:58,243
I don't know how I feel about that because I'm not sure that we should be trying to make it less detailed, but I'll go back and review those comments.

1311
01:51:59,903 --> 01:52:11,026
I did want to make sure that we put the sentence in because I think it's a good reminder to any elected official that by yourself, you're nothing, except if you're the mayor.

1312
01:52:11,326 --> 01:52:16,407
But a voting majority of the school committee shall exercise the following powers and perform the following duties.

1313
01:52:16,967 --> 01:52:21,688
And no individual member is empowered to act unless by vote of the school committee.

1314
01:52:22,408 --> 01:52:28,430
And to me, that's an extremely important reminder to those elected to the school committee that you are

1315
01:52:29,410 --> 01:52:35,453
part of city government and by yourself, you do not have a power.

1316
01:52:35,513 --> 01:52:43,757
You're not, as a school committee, you're not supposed to go to a department head and ask questions and boss them around, whatever.

1317
01:52:43,857 --> 01:52:44,817
So anyway.

1318
01:52:47,617 --> 01:52:52,819
Of the powers and duties, selection, evaluation, and removal of a superintendent is key.

1319
01:52:53,539 --> 01:52:55,499
Making policy is key.

1320
01:52:57,600 --> 01:53:01,421
And putting together the operating budget for the school system is key.

1321
01:53:01,561 --> 01:53:10,364
So those are really outlined in the first A, B, and C. And I'm going to leave the fine print for people to read.

1322
01:53:11,344 --> 01:53:12,525
Filling of vacancies.

1323
01:53:15,911 --> 01:53:25,174
try to be as consistent as what I've heard other language to be in descending, if it's an at large, it's in descending order of votes received by the candidate.

1324
01:53:27,454 --> 01:53:32,636
